SIMPLE: sharper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sharper
<hw>Sharp"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who bargains
closely, especially, one who cheats in bargains; a swinder; also, a
cheating gamester.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sharpers</qex>, as pikes, prey upon their own kind.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Swindler; cheat; deceiver; trickster; rogue. See
<er>Swindler</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sharpie</ent>⟦br⟧
